  "texts": [
    "However, this is an ideal case, and in practice, GAN does not meet the condition.",
    "So, the author Goodfellow et al. (2014) proposed an algorithm to update the discriminator multiple times (k) per generator's training update to get the discriminator close to an ideal.",
    "In vanilla GAN, the discriminator is updated only once (k = 1) per generator's training update which was suit- able for that specific experiment.",
    "Similarly, WGAN (Arjovsky et al. 2017) uses (k = 5) for discriminator updates per generator's training update for attaining an equilibrium state.",
    "It is a very critical and sensitive approach to control the training updates of the generator and discriminator models to reach a balanced state of training."
  ],
